{
  "text": "Ventilation-perfusion scintigraphy may be performed as the initial imaging examination if pulmonary CT angiography is contraindicated because the patient has an allergy to iodinated contrast media, renal insufficiency, or morbid obesity exceeding the weight limits of the CT scanner or if the patient cannot be moved to the imaging suite [CITATION_1] .",
